subject: Have you read...
text:
I signed up for the "Terms of Service" extension a number of months ago, and have YET to have been helped by it. It appears that, instead of doing the research yourself and then allowing us to benefit from it, you wait for each of your customers to do the research for you, thus having an extension built almost ENTIRELY by your customers...which, I, for one, refuse to do.

Can't you do any better than this???  This extension appears to be a rip-off of a service...i.e., promise something, get nothing.

-- 
tosdr.org | twitter.com/tosdr | github.com/tosdr
